    "Background": {
      "text": "Also known as \"Gamekeeper's thumb\" or \"Skier's thumb\"\nUlnar collateral ligament ruptures at insertion into proximal phalanx (due to radial deviation of MCP)\nIf left untreated, it will causes decreased thumb adduction and inability to perform opposition.\nThe mechanism of injury is usually a rapid deceleration while holding onto an object (such as a ski pole)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Swelling and localized tenderness over ulnar border of the thumb MCP joint\nWeakness of pinch",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
